PDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613430\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613430\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104han1665702687338.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/han1665702687338.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/han1665702687338.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"han1665702687338\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Current Occurrence Row Height (\n                              CurOccRowHeight)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Row height of the current occurrence in the Grid widget, in character cells or pixels. Default value is <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> (character cell).\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102716e1_d102717e1_d102718e1\">CurOccRowHeight<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">NumberOfCells</var> |\n        <var class=\"keyword varname\">NumberOfPixels</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__1\">Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__1\">&gt;= <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__2\">Number of cells; default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__1\">&gt;= <code class=\"ph codeph\">0px</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"han1665702687338__table_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1__entry__2\">Number of pixels </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"han1665702687338__section_vdq_ygb_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d357423e124\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102722e1_d102723e1_d102724e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Current Occurrence Row\n          Height</span> defines the height of a row when it becomes active. The previous active\n        row gets the initial row height, as defined by the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Row Height</span>\n        property, or the default row height, which is determined by the largest font that is used in\n        the row.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102725e1_d102726e1_d102727e1\">Setting a different row size for the current\n        occurrence can be useful for displaying data that is too long for one row, or for\n        highlighting the current occurrence.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"han1665702687338__section_ag3_1hb_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d357423e142\">Setting the Current Row Height</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"han1665702687338__ul_zg3_chb_wwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"han1665702687338__li_d41516e1_d41517e1_d41518e1\">When the row height is specified in cells, the height\n          is based on the Uniface Font 0, as specified by the Font0 setting in the\n            <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file. You can query the Font 0 cell height using\n            <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$cellinfo</span>. <p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102731e1_d102732e1_d102733e1\">To specify the row\n            height in cells, you must set an integer for the number of cells. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"han1665702687338__pre_ch3_chb_wwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=3\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102734e1_d102735e1_d102736e1\">Setting the row height to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n            resets the row height to its initial value.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"han1665702687338__li_d41519e1_d41520e1_d41521e1\">When the row height is specified in pixels, the\n          minimum height is the height of a cell in Font 0. If you specify a smaller value, it is\n          ignored. <p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102737e1_d102738e1_d102739e1\">To specify the row height in pixels, add\n              <code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code> after the value. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"han1665702687338__pre_eh3_chb_wwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=50px\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102740e1_d102741e1_d102742e1\">Setting the row height to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0px</code>\n            resets the row height to its initial value.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"han1665702687338__note_fh3_chb_wwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> You can query the Font 0 cell height\n      in pixels using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$cellinfo</span>.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102743e1_d102744e1_d102745e1\">Removing the CurOccRowHeight property from the\n        property string (as set in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file, or using\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$entityproperties</span>) resets the height of the rows to the initial\n        height.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102746e1_d102747e1_d102748e1\">Setting the property to an invalid value also resets\n        the row height to the initial value.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"han1665702687338__section_lct_4jb_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d357423e208\">Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102752e1_d102753e1_d102754e1\">You can set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Current Occurrence Row\n          Height</span> dynamically in ProcScript using the\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$entityproperties</span> function. For example, the following code sets the\n        row height for the ORDER_LINES entity to 3 character cells.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"han1665702687338__pre_cqw_qjb_wwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=3\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"han1665702687338__p_d102755e1_d102756e1_d102757e1\">To set the row height in pixels, specify\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">px</code>after the value. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"han1665702687338__pre_dqw_qjb_wwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=50px\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rdf1665702687207.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Row Height (RowHeight)</a><p>Height of each row in the Grid widget, in character cells or pixels. Default value is 1 (character cell).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dzl1665703006803.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$cellinfo</a><p>Get an associative list with the dimensions of a character cell in pixels.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlm1665702687704.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$entityproperties</a><p>Return or set the current representation properties of an entity.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613430\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613430\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Current Occurrence Row Height ( CurOccRowHeight) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Current Occurrence Row Height ( CurOccRowHeight) Row height of the current occurrence in the Grid widget, in character cells or pixels. Default value is 1 (character cell). CurOccRowHeight = \" NumberOfCells | NumberOfPixels px \" Value Description >= 0 Number of cells; default is 1 >= 0px Number of pixels Description The Current Occurrence Row Height defines the height of a row when it becomes active. The previous active row gets the initial row height, as defined by the Row Height property, or the default row height, which is determined by the largest font that is used in the row. Setting a different row size for the current occurrence can be useful for displaying data that is too long for one row, or for highlighting the current occurrence. Setting the Current Row Height When the row height is specified in cells, the height is based on the Uniface Font 0, as specified by the Font0 setting in the .ini file. You can query the Font 0 cell height using $cellinfo . To specify the row height in cells, you must set an integer for the number of cells. For example: $entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=3\" Copy Setting the row height to 0 resets the row height to its initial value. When the row height is specified in pixels, the minimum height is the height of a cell in Font 0. If you specify a smaller value, it is ignored. To specify the row height in pixels, add px after the value. For example: $entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=50px\" Copy Setting the row height to 0px resets the row height to its initial value. Tip: You can query the Font 0 cell height in pixels using $cellinfo . Removing the CurOccRowHeight property from the property string (as set in the .ini file, or using $entityproperties ) resets the height of the rows to the initial height. Setting the property to an invalid value also resets the row height to the initial value. Setting in ProcScript You can set Current Occurrence Row Height dynamically in ProcScript using the $entityproperties function. For example, the following code sets the row height for the ORDER_LINES entity to 3 character cells. $entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=3\" Copy To set the row height in pixels, specify px after the value. For example: $entityproperties(ORDER_LINES)=\"CurOccRowHeight=50px\" Copy Related Links Row Height (RowHeight) Height of each row in the Grid widget, in character cells or pixels. Default value is 1 (character cell). $cellinfo Get an associative list with the dimensions of a character cell in pixels. $entityproperties Return or set the current representation properties of an entity. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}